<link href="adcp.css" rel="stylesheet"><entry><xh5>let’s be having you • thanks for having me</xh5><p> <i>let’s be having you—</i>is used at public places as a request to move somewhere quickly: Ladies and gentlemen, <u>let’s be having you</u>: the museum closes in ten minutes.</p><p> <i>thanks for having me—</i>thank you for your hospitality <i>(said as one says goodbye): </i><u>Thanks for having me</u>, Jo—we’ve all had a lovely time!</p> </entry>
